arms. I have often attempted to explain, in later years, to learned andironical doctors, the strange, hideous, segmental quality of those pulsatingpangs that made a huge worm of me with limbs transformed into successivecoils of agony. By some fantastic fluke a third swimmer, a stranger, wasright behind me and helped to pull me out of an abysmal tangle of water-lilystems.

